ent color in Jamaican click beetles. The male beetles use the flashing to attract females for mating. Some males emit yellow light while males in a separated area have orange light.<\/p>\n\n<blockquote>\n  <p>Stoltz, U. et al. 2003. Darwinian natural selection for orange bioluminescent color in a Jamaican click beetle. Proceedings of the National Academy of Sciences USA 100: 14955-14959.<\/p>\n<\/blockquote>\n","answer_id":20751,"question_id":20745,"up_vote_count":1,"last_edit_date":1408915123},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/78f38914e0d07733567672a47c53904b?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG&f=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":8015,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/8015/hav0k","reputation":1090,"display_name":"Hav0k"},"score":0,"is_accepted":false,"down_vote_count":0,"last_activity_date":1408966628,"creation_date":1408966628,"body":"<p>Some species of fireflies (Lampyridae, Coleoptera) synchronize their light patterns during the mating procedure. <a href=\"http://www.nps.gov/grsm/naturescience/fireflies.htm\" rel=\"nofollow\">link<\/a><\/p>\n","answer_id":20763,"question_id":20745,"up_vote_count":0}],"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/questions/20745/does-bioluminescence-communcation-occur-on-macroscopic-level","last_activity_date":1408966628,"creation_date":1408906376,"answer_count":2,"title":"Does bioluminescence communcation occur on macroscopic level?","body":"<p>Some bacteria are known to communicate using bioluminescence (quorum sensing). Do we observe the same phenomena in any macroscopic species?<\/p>\n","question_id":20745,"tags":["bioluminescence"],"score":1,"down_vote_count":0,"is_answered":true,"view_count":35,"up_vote_count":1},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/ef839ab3e15beec085d4d9b811eba3fa?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"unregistered","user_id":8930,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/8930/pos","reputation":19,"display_name":"pos"},"closed_date":1409027368,"comments":[{"