is is similar. Some of these may have originated in America, but probably not all. Part of the problem is that tracking old disease requires those diseases to have symptoms obvious"},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/31f7489ce1ad16353c71abba83ae8be4?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":4747,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/4747/user137","reputation":3897,"display_name":"user137","accept_rate":78},"score":0,"post_id":20733,"edited":false,"creation_date":1408860091,"comment_id":32362,"body":"Comment too long... Obvious and unique enough for ancient physicians to recognize them, and for historians to recognize the description. Polio is kind of like that, with its paralysis. However, syphilis had symptoms similar to other diseases often described as leprosy before 1492. Hepatitis and encephelitis would be very difficult to distinguish from other illnesses, so it would be hard to rule out their presence in Europe before 1492."},{"owner":{"user_type":"does_not_exist","display_name":"user1357"},"score":0,"post_id":20733,"reply_to_user":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/31f7489ce1ad16353c71abba83ae8be4?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":4747,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/4747/user137","reputation":3897,"display_name":"user137","accept_rate":78},"edited":false,"creation_date":1408860202,"comment_id":32363,"body":"@user137 thank you i agree"},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://graph.facebook.com/100003927709763/picture?type=large","user_type":"registered","user_id":8942,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/8942/dan-sheppard","reputation":113,"display_name":"Dan Sheppard"},"score":1,"post_id":20733,"reply_to_user":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/31f7489ce1ad16353c71abba83ae8be4?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":4747,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/4747/user137","reputation":3897,"display_name":