 of plague do occur in rural environments, see this <a href=\"http://www.who.int/csr/don/archive/disease/plague/en/\" rel=\"nofollow\">WHO page<\/a> for some details. The WHO plays a role in responding to these outbreaks, as long as they are notified by the relevant countries. Plague infections respond well to antibiotic treatment.<\/p>\n\n<p>There has also been a <a href=\"http://www.vice.com/read/the-hot-zone-0000414-v21n8\" rel=\"nofollow\">recent outbreak in Madagascar<\/a>. According to the epidemiologists we are still in the midst of the 3rd plague pandemic, which started in China in the mid 19th century.<\/p>\n","answer_id":20708,"question_id":20706,"up_vote_count":4},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/c625f09c24ee8c9c270caa33cfd4ce7f?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG&f=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":4579,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/4579/har-wradim","reputation":2433,"display_name":"har-wradim"},"score":3,"is_accepted":false,"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/VmtoK.png?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":1320,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/1320/alan-boyd","reputation":17240,"display_name":"Alan Boyd"},"score":0,"post_id":20717,"edited":false,"creation_date":1408779433,"comment_id":32323,"body":"@har-wadim - very interesting - thanks!"}],"down_vote_count":0,"last_activity_date":1408753599,"creation_date":1408753599,"body":"<p>An addition to the Alan's answer:<\/p>\n\n<p>some sort of selection for more resistant genotypes inevitably did take place and left <a href=\"http://www.pnas.org/content/early/2014/01/30/1317723111\" rel=\"nofollow\">distinct footprints in the human populations<\/a>.<\/p>\n","answer_id":20717,"question_id":20706,"up_vote_count":3}],"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/questions/20706/why-isnt-bubonic-plague-as-virulent-as-it-once-was","last_activity_date":1408753599,"creation_date":1408722049,"answer_count":2,"title":"Why isn't Bubonic Plagu